but  for  audits,  like  you  mentioned,  I  mean,  we  have  a  very  thor-
ough—every  organization  I’ve  ever  belonged  to,  we  have  a  very 
thorough—what  we  call  ‘‘referencing  process,’’  where  an  audit  re-
port  is  referenced  back  to  supporting  work,  supporting  documents, 
interviews, what have you, and then a third party, not even associ-
ated  with  the  audit,  will  usually  come  in  and  do  a—what  we  call 
an  ‘‘independent  referencing,’’  checking  the  facts  and  figures  in 
every  report,  someone  who  wasn’t  even  involved  with  the  job—— 

Senator MCCASKILL. Clean read. 
Mr. CARSON. Yes, ma’am. 
